commit.message:
Remove generated files from repository

Not putting generated files into git is a good practice in general. In
this case, those files always showed up with diffs for me after building
guava, since my version of autoconf generates them with slightly
different content.

PackageInfo.g: drop unknown PostalAddress fields

This field is optional, so just dropping it seems better.

Switch makedoc.g to use AutoDoc

Use this to avoid duplicating the package version and release date in
doc/guava.xml, removing one potential source for mistakes when doing
releases.

The main advantage is that it removes the hard coded path to a GAP
executable, and also works correctly with ReleaseTools.

commit.message:
Use TmpName instead of TmpNameAllArchs

There are only differences between the two in older GAP versions, and
only in Cygwin. In recent GAP versions, the latter is just an alias for
the former, and `TmpNameAllArchs` has been deprecated. Indeed guava is
the last package still using it.

Remove reference to .zoo file format
